
[Richmond, 5? July 1780. JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 75 (5 July): The Speaker laid before the House a letter from the Governor,[482] enclosing several others from General Washington, and the committees of co-operation, respecting the state of the army. Read and referred to committee of the whole on the state of the commonwealth. TJs letter has not been located, and the letters it transmitted are not precisely identifiable.]
